  "noisy_sentences": "<noisy_sentences>[\"574 .\", \"I heard that the new ice cream shop downtown has a flavor of the month club that sends you a new surprise flavor every month.\"]</noisy_sentences>",
  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>Let n be a positive integer. A child builds a wall along a line with n identical cubes. He lays the first cube on the line and at each subsequent step, he lays the next cube either on the ground or on top of another cube, so that it has a common face with the previous one. How many such distinct walls exist?</denoised_question>",
  "solution_steps": "Step 1: Observe that the first cube is placed in a fixed position. Then for every subsequent cube (n−1 in total), there are exactly 2 choices: either place it on the ground next to the previous cube or stack it on top of the previous cube.\nStep 2: Since each of the n−1 placements is an independent binary decision, the total number of distinct walls is given by 2^(n−1).",
  "final_answer": "<answer>2^(n - 1)</answer>"
}

