  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>Three distinct vertices are randomly selected from the five vertices of a regular pentagon. Let p be the probability that the triangle formed by the chosen vertices is acute. Compute 10p.</denoised_question>",
  "solution_steps": "Step 1: The total number of triangles that can be formed from 5 vertices is C(5, 3) = 10.\\nStep 2: Label the vertices 0, 1, 2, 3, 4 in cyclic order. A triangle inscribed in a circle (vertices of the pentagon lie on a circle) will be obtuse if one of its arcs (the minor arc between two adjacent chosen vertices) is 180° or more. In a regular pentagon, each central angle is 72°. An arc spanning 3 vertices (i.e. 3×72° = 216° as a major arc, but its complementary minor arc is 360° - 216° = 144°) needs careful checking, so we directly list the triangles and their arcs.\\nStep 3: List the triangles and determine if they are acute by checking the three minor arcs: the triangle is acute if all three arcs (the arcs between the consecutive vertices along the circle) are less than 180°.\\nConsidering the triangles (using vertices 0, 1, 2, 3, 4 in order):\\n- Triangle (0, 1, 2): Arcs are 72°, 72°, and 360° - (72+72) = 216° → Obtuse.\\n- Triangle (0, 1, 3): Arcs: between 0→1: 72°, 1→3: 144° (skipping vertex 2), and 3→0: 360° - (72+144) = 144° → Acute.\\n- Triangle (0, 1, 4): Arcs: 72°, 144°, 144° → Acute.\\n- Triangle (0, 2, 3): Arcs: 144°, 72°, 144° → Acute.\\n- Triangle (0, 2, 4): Arcs: 144°, 144°, 72° → Acute.\\n- Triangle (0, 3, 4): Arcs: 216° (from 0 to 3), 72°, 72° → Obtuse.\\n- Triangle (1, 2, 3): Arcs: 72°, 72°, 216° → Obtuse.\\n- Triangle (1, 2, 4): Arcs: 72°, 144°, 144° → Acute.\\n- Triangle (1, 3, 4): Arcs: 144°, 72°, 144° → Acute.\\n- Triangle (2, 3, 4): Arcs: 72°, 72°, 216° → Obtuse.\\nStep 4: Count the acute triangles: They are (0, 1, 3), (0, 1, 4), (0, 2, 3), (0, 2, 4), (1, 2, 4), and (1, 3, 4) giving 6 acute triangles.\\nStep 5: The probability p that a randomly selected triangle is acute is 6/10 = 3/5.\\nStep 6: Compute 10p = 10 × (3/5) = 6.",
  "final_answer": "<answer>6</answer>"
}

