  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>In an equilateral triangle with side length 10, a point P inside the triangle has distances 1 and 3 from two of its sides. Find the distance from P to the third side.</denoised_question>",
  "solution_steps": "1. In any equilateral triangle, the sum of the perpendicular distances from any interior point to the three sides is constant and equal to the altitude of the triangle. 2. The altitude (h) of an equilateral triangle with side length s is given by h = (sqrt(3)/2)*s. For s = 10, h = (sqrt(3)/2)*10 = 5√3. 3. Let the distances from the point P to the three sides be d1, d2, and d3. Given d1 = 1 and d2 = 3, we have d1 + d2 + d3 = 5√3. 4. Therefore, d3 = 5√3 - 1 - 3 = 5√3 - 4.",
  "final_answer": "<answer>5√3 - 4</answer>"
}

