  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>How many interior intersection points are there on a 12 by 12 grid of squares?</denoised_question>",
  "solution_steps": "A grid of squares is formed by drawing lines that create the squares. In a grid with m by n squares, the total number of intersection points (including boundary points) is (m+1)×(n+1). However, interior intersection points are those that do not lie along the boundary. To find these, subtract the boundary intersections, yielding (m-1)×(n-1). For a 12 by 12 grid, m = n = 12, so the number of interior intersection points is (12 - 1)×(12 - 1) = 11×11 = 121.",
  "final_answer": "<answer>121</answer>"
}

{
