  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>In a regular decagon A₀A₁A₂...A₉, compute the measure of ∠A₀A₃A₇.</denoised_question>",
  "solution_steps": "1. Note that in a regular decagon, the vertices lie on a circle and the central angle between consecutive vertices is 360°/10 = 36°.\n2. The inscribed angle ∠A₀A₃A₇ is determined by the arc between A₀ and A₇ that does not include the vertex A₃. \n3. Calculate the smaller arc between A₀ and A₇. The smaller difference in vertex indices is min(|7 - 0|, 10 - |7 - 0|) = min(7, 3) = 3. Therefore, the arc measure is 3 × 36° = 108°.\n4. The measure of an inscribed angle is half the measure of its intercepted arc. Thus, ∠A₀A₃A₇ = 108°/2 = 54°.",
  "final_answer": "<answer>54°</answer>"
}

